<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-27T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-27T18:36:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15316.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-27T17:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>By special messenger: Zapata forces defeated Carranza forces in Mexico
                            City. Capital entirely cut off from the world. Carranza rushing all
                            available men to Mexico City. If Zapata forces are driven back I fear
                            horrors will follow. No food in Mexico City.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>